WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.234
<i>The 1970s were
an awesome time to be a kid.</i>

00:04.297 --> 00:06.179
<i>It was the Wild West.</i>

00:06.234 --> 00:08.402
<i>Bike helmets hadn't been
invented yet or car seatbelts</i>

00:08.436 --> 00:11.105
<i>or even normal adult supervision.</i>

00:11.139 --> 00:13.107
<i>Dads weren't around
as much as they are now.</i>

00:13.141 --> 00:15.109
<i>And my mom was busy running the house.</i>

00:15.143 --> 00:18.546
<i>She had a lot on her plate
and no time for tomfoolery...</i>

00:18.580 --> 00:19.547
<i>whatever that is.</i>

00:19.581 --> 00:21.148
<i>There were eight of us boys,</i>

00:21.182 --> 00:23.884
<i>including my oldest brother,
just home from college.</i>

00:23.919 --> 00:26.487
<i>That's a lot of testosterone
under one roof.</i>

00:28.782 --> 00:32.279
<font color="#0080ff">Synced & corrected by</font> kinglouisxx
<font color="#0080ff">www.</font>addic7ed<font color="#0080ff">.com</font>

00:32.350 --> 00:34.161
Timmy, wipe the crumbs off that
and bring it here.

00:34.195 --> 00:35.796
You think we're made of foil?

00:35.830 --> 00:36.764
Hey!

00:36.798 --> 00:38.354
I've got an important surprise
in the car.

00:38.409 --> 00:40.801
Who wants to help carry it in?
Eddie, Frank, you do.

00:40.835 --> 00:43.170
<i>Like dads since cavemen days...</i>

00:43.204 --> 00:44.972
- Oh, boy.
- <i>...mine loved the heroic feeling</i>

00:45.006 --> 00:47.271
<i>of bringing something home
intended to make life easier</i>

00:47.330 --> 00:48.263
<i>for his mate.</i>

00:48.287 --> 00:49.910
We are the proud recipients

00:49.945 --> 00:52.090
of our very own dielectric oven.

00:52.131 --> 00:55.033
It heats food using
small wavelength radiation.

00:55.067 --> 00:56.768
- Radiation?
- Micro-waves.

00:56.802 --> 00:58.202
- Over here on the counter.
- On the counter?

00:58.237 --> 00:59.270
Where am I supposed to put the baby

00:59.304 --> 01:00.359
when I'm chopping things?

01:00.375 --> 01:03.010
Right up here on top.
It's a prototype from the plant.

01:03.044 --> 01:04.678
Mr. Crane selected us
to be among the first families

01:04.712 --> 01:06.614
to try it out. Here you go, William.

01:06.648 --> 01:08.048
So we're guinea pigs.

01:08.083 --> 01:10.050
We're pioneers. Like Neil Armstrong.

01:10.085 --> 01:11.785
And just like the astronauts,

01:11.820 --> 01:13.153
we need to log our experiences.

01:13.188 --> 01:15.689
Plus any physical symptoms
that may arise.

01:15.714 --> 01:16.657
Symptoms?

01:16.691 --> 01:18.459
"Dizziness, wounds that won't heal,

01:18.493 --> 01:20.227
blurred vision, impotence,
hallucinations..."

01:20.261 --> 01:22.863
Thank you, but I don't think
I need this.

01:22.897 --> 01:24.328
It'll cut your cooking time in half.

01:24.392 --> 01:26.233
You had a chance to
cut my cooking time in half

01:26.267 --> 01:27.835
- four kids ago.
- You are gonna love it.

01:27.869 --> 01:28.969
Just don't put any metal in it.

01:29.004 --> 01:31.038
- I don't want to put anything in it.
- Why no metal?

01:31.072 --> 01:33.073
Well, the scientific
explanation's complicated,

01:33.108 --> 01:35.142
but the dad explanation is "shut up."

01:35.176 --> 01:37.144
This kind of technology
helps defend America.

01:37.178 --> 01:38.182
Then count me in.

01:38.207 --> 01:39.980
It'll cook a hot dog in 30 seconds.

01:40.015 --> 01:41.980
In a war, our boys will have eaten

01:42.012 --> 01:44.199
and launched their missiles while
the Soviets are still

01:44.238 --> 01:45.941
- boiling their dog water.
- Nice.

01:48.088 --> 01:49.422
That's unbelievable.

01:51.092 --> 01:53.172
I know. I know. I'll make myself scarce.

01:53.197 --> 01:55.829
It's okay. Come in. Close the door.

01:55.864 --> 01:58.565
<i>Joey was two years older,
and it was pretty huge</i>

01:58.600 --> 02:00.434
<i>being invited in
on some secret between him</i>

02:00.468 --> 02:02.536
<i>and his ultra-sophisticated
friend Davey.</i>

02:02.561 --> 02:05.764
Hello, Timothy.

02:07.366 --> 02:08.633
What's the skinny?

02:08.667 --> 02:10.001
You know Barbara Eden,

02:10.035 --> 02:11.993
- the genie from "I Dream of Jeannie"?
- Yeah.

02:12.025 --> 02:14.172
Well, Davey's cousin in Maine
called long distance

02:14.206 --> 02:16.207
to tell him to watch
a certain show she's on tonight.

02:16.242 --> 02:17.562
It's on three hours earlier back there

02:17.587 --> 02:19.677
'cause they're all
stupid farmers or something.

02:20.713 --> 02:23.047
Apparently, she's dancing,

02:23.082 --> 02:24.492
and in the middle of it her clothes rip

02:24.517 --> 02:29.154
or something because...
according to Davey's cousin...

02:29.188 --> 02:31.790
you can see everything.

02:34.026 --> 02:35.560
Everything?

02:35.594 --> 02:37.228
Everything.

02:38.998 --> 02:41.132
In the world?

02:43.269 --> 02:45.136
Okay, your brother doesn't
know jack about girls.

02:45.171 --> 02:46.838
I guess not. Let's go.

02:46.872 --> 02:50.241
<i>And just like that,
I was on the outside again.</i>

02:50.276 --> 02:52.243
<i>I didn't figure out
what they meant by "everything"</i>

02:52.278 --> 02:54.212
<i>until it was way too late.</i>

02:56.081 --> 02:58.049
Oh!

02:58.083 --> 03:00.852
Guys!

03:00.886 --> 03:02.253
This will free up all kinds of time

03:02.288 --> 03:03.121
to do the stuff you enjoy...

03:03.155 --> 03:05.056
laundry, sewing, cleaning the house.

03:05.090 --> 03:06.858
You'll be the envy of all your friends.

03:06.892 --> 03:08.226
I'm expected to get friends now, too?

03:08.260 --> 03:09.427
Watch what it does with an egg.

03:12.064 --> 03:13.398
Is that a microwave oven?

03:13.432 --> 03:15.600
See? The whole town's talking about it.

03:15.634 --> 03:16.601
Oh.

03:20.239 --> 03:22.173
Oh, Mike, I don't need this.

03:22.208 --> 03:23.241
I promise, if you don't like it
by tomorrow,

03:23.275 --> 03:25.677
you can keep trying.
Eventually, you'll like it.

03:25.711 --> 03:27.445
I didn't realize these were
approved for home use.

03:27.479 --> 03:29.681
They're not. They take up
too much counter space.

03:29.715 --> 03:30.615
Why is the egg shaking?

03:30.649 --> 03:33.351
It's excited
about innovative technology!

03:35.387 --> 03:36.554
Jiminy Christmas!

03:39.124 --> 03:40.291
Outstanding!

03:40.326 --> 03:42.694
Here.

03:42.728 --> 03:43.695
You clean up the egg stuff,

03:43.729 --> 03:45.463
then let's blow up an orange.

03:47.733 --> 03:50.268
Doesn't sound like
Dad's listening to you, Mom.

03:50.302 --> 03:51.436
You know you have a right to be heard.

03:51.470 --> 03:53.238
Look at you, sticking your nose in

03:53.272 --> 03:54.639
between me and your father.

03:54.673 --> 03:56.598
You aiming for a broken home
or a broken jaw?

03:56.623 --> 03:57.834
<i>When you said something to my mom</i>

03:57.866 --> 04:00.087
<i>that she didn't want to hear,
she tended to respond with hostility.</i>

04:00.112 --> 04:01.302
<i>The more hostility,</i>

04:01.327 --> 04:02.814
<i>the more you knew
you were onto something.</i>

04:02.848 --> 04:04.415
I've just been
reading some psychology and...

04:04.450 --> 04:05.917
Okay. I'll stop you right there.

04:05.951 --> 04:07.283
Your dad and I
don't have any psychology.

04:07.308 --> 04:10.488
We were raised in the Depression
and had to do without.

04:10.522 --> 04:12.657
I got this orange
from Mrs. Strausser's tree.

04:12.691 --> 04:15.293
It dropped on our side after
I beat the branch with a rake.

04:15.327 --> 04:17.095
- We also got a new Frisbee.
- Lawrence read a book

04:17.129 --> 04:19.096
and thinks he can
analyze our psychology.

04:19.130 --> 04:21.666
Oh, don't waste your time.
We're 100% normal.

04:21.700 --> 04:24.669
Now let's make this fruit ball go boom.

04:26.138 --> 04:28.106
I should really cut down on these.

04:28.140 --> 04:30.108
Mm, you know what? Try one of mine.

04:30.142 --> 04:32.277
- They're mild.
- Hmm.

04:32.311 --> 04:34.112
Chicago should be
getting their glimpse of Eden

04:34.146 --> 04:36.180
right about now.

04:36.215 --> 04:39.150
<i>Unlike nowadays when
every aspect of female anatomy</i>

04:39.184 --> 04:40.610
<i>is only a mouse-click away,</i>

04:40.635 --> 04:44.727
<i>in 1972 the level of ignorance
in a house with all boys</i>

04:44.752 --> 04:45.766
<i>was staggering.</i>

04:45.791 --> 04:47.158
I know what you guys were talking about.

04:47.192 --> 04:48.860
What show is Barbara Eden
gonna be on tonight?

04:48.894 --> 04:52.130
We can't let you in on this.
It might scar you.

04:52.164 --> 04:53.298
Well, I wanna be scarred.

04:53.332 --> 04:55.700
Tell me.

04:55.734 --> 04:57.869
"The Bob Hope Special," 9:00.

04:57.903 --> 05:00.305
And according to my cousin,
you can see it all.

05:00.339 --> 05:01.673
The whole kit and caboodle.

05:01.707 --> 05:03.174
Both?

05:05.210 --> 05:06.377
Obviously you don't know much,

05:06.412 --> 05:08.095
so let me teach you the basics.

05:08.120 --> 05:10.615
First off, girls' penises

05:10.649 --> 05:12.383
are totally different from ours...

05:15.530 --> 05:17.357
Food's ready!

05:17.444 --> 05:19.623
Possibly. No guarantees.

05:23.186 --> 05:24.920
Look at us!

05:24.972 --> 05:27.189
It's like dinnertime on Apollo 16.

05:27.262 --> 05:28.796
So far, this thing
hasn't saved me one minute.

05:28.831 --> 05:29.916
And every time I turn it on,

05:29.941 --> 05:31.966
the neighborhood dogs
circle the house and bark.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.235
Seriously?

05:35.671 --> 05:37.872
- That is valuable data.
- Yeah.

05:37.906 --> 05:41.542
William, make a note.
Dogs love the microwave.

05:41.577 --> 05:43.544
Get away from our house!

05:43.579 --> 05:45.112
Timmy and I call the TV for tonight.

05:45.147 --> 05:47.949
We got a show we want to watch.
It's... educational.

05:47.983 --> 05:49.917
Sorry, there's a program
I'm looking forward to.

05:49.952 --> 05:51.919
- Mom, no!
- "The Bob Hope Special" is on.

05:51.954 --> 05:52.854
Okay, your house, your rules.

05:52.888 --> 05:54.789
That man helped us win three wars.

05:54.823 --> 05:55.990
If it weren't for Bob, you'd be watching

05:56.024 --> 05:57.146
"The Ho Chi Minh Show" tonight.

05:57.201 --> 05:58.364
Peg, maybe tomorrow you can

05:58.420 --> 05:59.994
microwave that casserole thing you do,

06:00.028 --> 06:01.285
you know, with the tater-tots,

06:01.310 --> 06:02.630
chipped beef, and the French dressing...

06:02.664 --> 06:04.298
Give away my recipe, why don't you?

06:04.333 --> 06:05.733
No, tomorrow night, we're going to

06:05.767 --> 06:07.802
the Hawaiian Luau Dinner Dance
at the church.

06:07.836 --> 06:09.804
Sorry, Peg. That dinner thing's a no.

06:09.838 --> 06:11.606
I promised the boys I'd take
them to the Dodger game.

06:12.875 --> 06:13.608
It's Bat Night!

06:13.642 --> 06:15.443
I told you about this weeks ago.

06:15.477 --> 06:16.811
Was the TV on?

06:16.845 --> 06:19.447
'Cause if it was, that's on you.

06:19.481 --> 06:20.815
Yeah, well,
bring me a bat from Bat Night

06:20.849 --> 06:22.083
so I can get your attention.

06:22.117 --> 06:23.451
<i>My mom didn't socialize often</i>

06:23.485 --> 06:25.086
<i>because she didn't much like people,</i>

06:25.120 --> 06:26.687
<i>but the occasional dinner out
with my dad</i>

06:26.722 --> 06:28.489
<i>was something she looked forward to.</i>

06:28.524 --> 06:29.957
This pizza's like rubber.

06:29.992 --> 06:32.386
It's better this way.
Makes eating it last longer.

06:32.411 --> 06:33.694
Ow! I burnt my tongue.

06:33.729 --> 06:37.298
Yeah, mine's frozen solid.
Peggy, what did you do wrong?

06:37.332 --> 06:38.503
What I did wrong was let you

06:38.528 --> 06:40.434
bring that crazy food robot
into my home.

06:40.469 --> 06:41.836
All right, tonight after supper,

06:41.870 --> 06:43.471
William and I are gonna
roll up our sleeves

06:43.505 --> 06:45.273
and tackle this thing.

06:45.307 --> 06:47.708
Call your wife.
Tell her you might be home late.

06:49.144 --> 06:51.212
This fish stick is burning my tongue!

06:51.246 --> 06:54.215
Here. Ice it down with this.

06:54.249 --> 06:56.617
All right, William, cream of tomato soup

06:56.652 --> 06:59.887
at two minutes... warm and savory.

06:59.922 --> 07:04.292
Two minutes, four seconds...
Manson crime scene.

07:05.894 --> 07:07.161
"Manson crime scene."

07:08.997 --> 07:11.365
Everything all right
in my kitchen, Mike?

07:11.400 --> 07:13.067
Never better!

07:13.101 --> 07:16.230
<i>Welcome to the Bob
Hope Summer Extravaganza.</i>

07:18.840 --> 07:20.875
You boys seem awfully excited.

07:20.909 --> 07:22.910
It's an extravaganza.

07:22.945 --> 07:25.079
That means there's extra vaganza.

07:26.348 --> 07:27.715
Oh, is it cool if my friend Davey

07:27.749 --> 07:28.983
comes over and watches with us?

07:29.017 --> 07:30.251
Of course Davey's welcome.

07:30.285 --> 07:32.420
I know this is the time of night
his mother gets into her wine.

07:32.454 --> 07:33.554
And when that woman gets started...

07:33.579 --> 07:34.546
Hello, Davey!

07:34.571 --> 07:35.828
Hey. Hi, Mrs. Cleary.
Thanks for having me over.

07:35.853 --> 07:37.562
You mind if I watch this?
My mom's watching something else.

07:37.587 --> 07:39.035
- So she was awake when you left, then?
- Yes.

07:39.063 --> 07:40.018
That's encouraging.

07:40.043 --> 07:42.830
We fixed it so the neighborhood
dogs stop barking.

07:42.864 --> 07:43.831
Who's up for a baked potato?

07:43.865 --> 07:46.000
No one wants a baked potato
at 9:00 at night.

07:46.034 --> 07:47.201
This isn't Europe.

07:47.235 --> 07:49.036
A dessert potato?

07:49.071 --> 07:50.237
Take five minutes to think about it.

07:50.272 --> 07:51.872
The potatoes will be done in two!

07:51.907 --> 07:52.807
Let's light 'em up.

07:52.841 --> 07:55.176
The gang out there
is hollering for taters!

07:55.210 --> 07:56.473
Wow, you're really invested

07:56.497 --> 07:57.411
in that device, Dad.

07:57.412 --> 07:59.046
Oh, it's an honor.
I was the first employee

07:59.081 --> 08:01.248
Mr. Crane asked to test it
after Bob Brogan chickened out

08:01.283 --> 08:02.350
because of the metal plate in his head.

08:02.384 --> 08:05.586
Poor Bob Brogan. A plate
in his head and no microwave.

08:05.621 --> 08:06.587
Hmm.

08:06.622 --> 08:08.094
<i>I've heard of Off-Broadway,</i>

08:08.119 --> 08:10.124
<i>but this is ridiculous.</i>

08:10.158 --> 08:12.266
<i>One year you don't send
a Christmas card to your agent,</i>

08:12.291 --> 08:13.227
<i>look where he sends you.</i>

08:13.252 --> 08:14.508
If you boys really don't like this,

08:14.533 --> 08:16.030
I guess we can turn on something else.

08:16.055 --> 08:17.089
- Oh, no!
- No. No, we love it.

08:17.132 --> 08:18.799
It's... We're laughing on the inside.

08:18.834 --> 08:21.402
<i>It was quite a trip.
Eight hours for flight</i>

08:21.436 --> 08:22.803
<i>and two days to get your luggage.</i>

08:25.607 --> 08:27.408
- Luggage.
- Yeah.

08:27.442 --> 08:30.811
<i>We'll be right back.</i>

08:32.614 --> 08:34.782
I just mean that
your sense of selfworth is...

08:34.816 --> 08:36.317
is maybe tied to your work.

08:36.351 --> 08:38.219
What's tied to it is my paycheck.

08:38.253 --> 08:39.986
Well, it looks like Mr. Crane's regard

08:40.022 --> 08:41.822
- is really important to you.
- It's because he's my friend.

08:41.857 --> 08:44.158
And what does your friend
Mr. Crane call you?

08:44.192 --> 08:45.960
He calls me "Mike"...

08:45.994 --> 08:47.495
...'cause we're friends.

08:47.529 --> 08:49.330
Aah! Man overboard!

08:49.364 --> 08:50.731
We'll give that one to Davey.

08:50.766 --> 08:51.899
<i>Our next guest comes to us</i>

08:51.933 --> 08:53.901
<i>straight from inside her bottle.</i>

08:53.935 --> 08:55.403
Just like Davey's mom.

08:55.437 --> 08:57.405
<i>Please welcome one dynamite lady,</i>

08:57.439 --> 08:59.140
<i>Miss Barbara Eden.</i>

08:59.174 --> 09:02.429
♪ <i>What goes up got to come down</i> ♪

09:02.484 --> 09:04.412
A tiny delay on the spuds, boys.

09:04.446 --> 09:05.613
- ♪ <i>Spinning wheel got to go 'round</i> ♪
- Peggy, we have any chives?

09:05.647 --> 09:06.814
I'm watching a show.

09:06.848 --> 09:08.983
Well, your kitchen's a mess.
Frankly, I can't find anything.

09:09.017 --> 09:11.619
♪ <i>Talking 'bout your troubles,</i>
<i>it's a crying sin</i> ♪

09:11.653 --> 09:15.456
♪ <i>Ride a painted pony,</i>
<i>let the spinning wheel spin</i> ♪

09:15.490 --> 09:16.991
We all right with you kids
watching this?

09:17.025 --> 09:20.194
- ♪ <i>Got no money and you got no home</i> ♪
- It's America's Bob Hope.

09:20.228 --> 09:22.196
♪ <i>Spinning wheel</i> ♪

09:22.230 --> 09:23.931
♪ <i>All alone</i> ♪

09:23.965 --> 09:27.935
Oh, for the love of Pete!

09:31.339 --> 09:32.340
What's that?

09:32.365 --> 09:34.375
I tried to heat up some cobbler.

09:34.409 --> 09:36.210
You ruined my best Tupperware.

09:36.244 --> 09:37.945
No, it's an old margarine tub.

09:37.979 --> 09:40.881
Exactly, my best Tupperware.

09:40.916 --> 09:42.850
See what I mean
about the mess in there, Peg?

09:44.453 --> 09:47.321
<i>My mom always tried her
best to avoid arguing with my dad,</i>

09:47.355 --> 09:52.159
<i>but she had ways of
expressing herself nonverbally.</i>

09:53.495 --> 09:55.024
<i>Not the best approach</i>

09:55.048 --> 09:56.170
<i>to conflict resolution...</i>

09:56.195 --> 09:57.865
<i>...but better than her first choice...</i>

09:57.890 --> 10:00.192
<i>throwing it at his head.</i>

10:00.235 --> 10:02.236
W-Wait. W-W-What's happening?

10:02.270 --> 10:04.171
This happens sometimes.
Wiggle the antennae.

10:06.541 --> 10:08.476
Not up and down. Side to side.

10:08.510 --> 10:10.068
Is that better?
No, it's worse. That's worse.

10:10.093 --> 10:11.645
- Go back to where you were.
- What?!

10:11.680 --> 10:13.756
No, no. Davey, this way,
this way, this way.

10:13.781 --> 10:15.216
The microwave!

10:15.250 --> 10:16.984
Oh, no.

10:20.622 --> 10:22.590
No! Move it this way! Move it... Yeah!

10:22.624 --> 10:23.591
Yeah!

10:23.625 --> 10:25.059
- Yes!
- Yes!

10:30.465 --> 10:34.025
N-o-o-o-o-o!

10:35.657 --> 10:37.257
Oatmeal, Mike?

10:37.330 --> 10:39.087
Have to warn you,
it'll be 30 seconds longer

10:39.181 --> 10:40.665
since we don't have that thing anymore.

10:40.700 --> 10:44.469
It's interesting.
You know what I found in here?

10:44.503 --> 10:45.746
Something metal.

10:45.785 --> 10:47.597
- Something metal?
- How could that have happened?

10:47.637 --> 10:49.372
- I don't know.
- Hmm.

10:49.406 --> 10:50.339
But I have a theory.

10:50.374 --> 10:54.643
Me too. What's yours?
We'll see if they match.

10:54.678 --> 10:55.845
Has to be one of the kids.

10:55.879 --> 10:57.680
Bingo.

10:57.714 --> 10:58.948
Probably not Andy, though.

11:00.751 --> 11:03.352
Probably.

11:03.387 --> 11:05.154
Maybe there'll be a rerun?

11:05.188 --> 11:06.856
Not after grown-ups get wind of this.

11:06.890 --> 11:08.691
I heard the camera man got arrested.

11:08.725 --> 11:11.727
If only there was a way
to see something on TV again

11:11.762 --> 11:13.729
after it's already been on.

11:13.764 --> 11:16.165
That technology exists, gentlemen.

11:16.199 --> 11:17.566
My brother was watching
at his friend's last night,

11:17.601 --> 11:19.702
- and he took a picture.
- No way.

11:19.736 --> 11:20.738
Right at the moment of truth.

11:20.763 --> 11:21.939
Oh, my God! Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

11:21.964 --> 11:23.672
- Be cool.
- Sorry.

11:23.707 --> 11:25.708
Now, listen, if we rush
to the drug store right now,

11:25.742 --> 11:27.510
we get it back in no time. 10 days tops.

11:27.544 --> 11:29.078
No. We go to Fotomat.

11:29.112 --> 11:30.312
For a little extra bread,

11:30.347 --> 11:33.516
you get your pictures in 24 hours.

11:33.550 --> 11:34.550
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

11:34.584 --> 11:37.720
All Cleary boys to the living room! Now!

11:37.754 --> 11:41.357
All right, smartest thing
the guilty party could do

11:41.391 --> 11:44.060
would be confess before
I even bring up the crime.

11:44.094 --> 11:45.661
I did it.

11:45.695 --> 11:47.763
- You did?
- I think so.

11:47.798 --> 11:48.764
Then what did you do?

11:48.799 --> 11:51.767
I don't really know.
I kind of just panicked.

11:51.802 --> 11:55.538
Someone put something metal
in our very important microwave

11:55.572 --> 11:56.672
and broke it.

11:56.706 --> 11:58.441
Oh, no. I didn't do that.

11:58.475 --> 12:00.342
Someone did it.
And we're not leaving this room

12:00.377 --> 12:02.545
until your dad and I
find out who it was.

12:02.579 --> 12:03.679
I'll stay here all night.

12:03.713 --> 12:04.580
Can we watch TV?

12:04.614 --> 12:05.781
Try it.

12:05.816 --> 12:08.217
- Try turning it on.
- I'm good.

12:08.251 --> 12:10.619
- Can I pee?
- Nope.

12:10.654 --> 12:13.022
That microwave
was a technological marvel,

12:13.056 --> 12:14.623
a wonder of modern science,

12:14.658 --> 12:17.226
and then some fiend destroyed it.

12:17.260 --> 12:18.928
Frankly, I'm disgusted.

12:18.962 --> 12:20.563
And since none of you are man enough

12:20.597 --> 12:21.764
to admit to your crime,

12:21.798 --> 12:23.732
the Dodger game tonight is off.

12:23.767 --> 12:25.601
- What?!
- Are you serious? But it's Bat Night!

12:25.635 --> 12:28.237
Oh... I know.

12:28.271 --> 12:31.640
Mike, it doesn't seem right
to punish everyone

12:31.675 --> 12:33.609
because your contraption got ruined

12:33.643 --> 12:35.778
in a mystery we may never solve.

12:35.812 --> 12:37.746
No confession, no Dodgers.

12:40.016 --> 12:41.817
Okay.

12:41.852 --> 12:43.986
Look, um... I'm sorry.

12:44.020 --> 12:46.222
Uh... the truth is...

12:46.256 --> 12:47.790
Instead, your mom and I are gonna go

12:47.824 --> 12:48.791
to that stupid dinner dance.

12:48.825 --> 12:50.559
It's exactly the right call.

12:50.594 --> 12:52.128
You boys will thank us one day.

12:52.162 --> 12:53.796
I'm gonna go pick out a dress.

