13:04.348 --> 13:07.706
Hi. I'm here to drop off pictures.

13:07.768 --> 13:09.979
Cool. What's the name?

13:10.004 --> 13:11.665
Jorgellington.

13:13.016 --> 13:15.084
"J," like Jackson.

13:15.109 --> 13:18.111
- Okay.
- "O," like ostrich.

13:20.957 --> 13:23.526
How much more dancing
until we get to sit down?

13:23.560 --> 13:26.529
You're not any worse
than any of the other husbands.

13:26.563 --> 13:28.130
Except for Herb Milbank.

13:28.165 --> 13:31.934
He and Katy took lessons
at Arthur Murray.

13:31.968 --> 13:33.135
What a loser.

13:33.170 --> 13:34.470
Sad, really.

13:36.873 --> 13:38.874
I guess I'm still bugged
about the microwave.

13:38.909 --> 13:41.710
No one has a right
to be more upset than me.

13:41.745 --> 13:44.280
I'm the one who doesn't
get to use it anymore.

13:44.314 --> 13:47.052
Aloha. Ahiahi, Mike and Peggy.

13:47.077 --> 13:48.284
Concentrate.

13:50.921 --> 13:53.889
You'd think they'd be embarrassed.

13:53.924 --> 13:56.125
I'm kicking myself now

13:56.159 --> 13:57.693
for not ordering the double prints.

13:57.727 --> 13:59.995
My friend Todd's a good tracer.

14:00.030 --> 14:01.830
He can mock something up
for us pretty quickly.

14:01.865 --> 14:05.301
Hey. A lot of whispering going
on between you two lately.

14:05.335 --> 14:07.069
Anything you'd care to open up about?

14:07.103 --> 14:09.872
What? We weren't whispering.

14:09.906 --> 14:10.940
Guys, can you come in here a minute?

14:14.344 --> 14:15.711
- The Dodgers are on.
- Yeah.

14:15.745 --> 14:18.881
Circle up. It'll just take a second.

14:18.915 --> 14:19.682
I want to rap.

14:19.716 --> 14:21.717
Oh, geez. He's sitting backwards.

14:21.751 --> 14:23.352
Sensing a bad vibe in the house

14:23.386 --> 14:25.721
about what happened to the microwave.

14:25.755 --> 14:28.357
Now, I'm not interested in placing blame

14:28.391 --> 14:29.758
or narcing on anyone...

14:29.793 --> 14:30.926
Then I'm out.

14:30.961 --> 14:33.329
...but I believe that Dad

14:33.363 --> 14:36.932
put a lot of his self-worth
inside that little, metal box.

14:36.967 --> 14:40.769
And whoever blew it up,
in a way, also blew up Dad.

14:40.804 --> 14:42.938
And, until he gets closure on this,

14:42.973 --> 14:44.573
it's gonna be really hard for him,

14:44.608 --> 14:46.596
and he's just gonna keep
punishing everybody.

14:46.631 --> 14:48.787
Like you not letting us
watch the Dodger game?

14:48.812 --> 14:52.748
So, if any of us is carrying
around a heavy secret,

14:52.782 --> 14:55.251
I'm here to facilitate
getting it off your chest.

14:55.285 --> 14:56.885
I haven't read the whole Bible,

14:56.920 --> 14:58.887
but pretty sure
when you quit the seminary,

14:58.922 --> 15:00.789
you lose your confession license.

15:00.824 --> 15:03.359
Right on. I've said my piece.

15:03.393 --> 15:04.326
Wait a minute.

15:04.361 --> 15:07.196
- Yes, William?
- Has it occurred to you that

15:07.230 --> 15:10.599
maybe you're throwing all this
psychology at everybody else

15:10.634 --> 15:13.035
as a way of ignoring your own issues?

15:13.069 --> 15:15.404
What do you... What do you mean?

15:15.438 --> 15:17.573
It seems like since
you gave up the priesthood,

15:17.607 --> 15:19.375
you've lost your sense of identity,

15:19.409 --> 15:20.943
so you started poking at all of us

15:20.977 --> 15:23.579
because it's scary to look at yourself

15:23.613 --> 15:26.738
and realize that
you're not that special anymore.

15:26.850 --> 15:28.879
Do you think maybe
that's what's going on here?

15:33.923 --> 15:36.258
Heavy truths from a tiny man.

15:36.293 --> 15:37.926
You've given me a lot to chew on.

15:37.961 --> 15:39.995
Thanks, buddy.

15:42.999 --> 15:46.969
That was amazing. How did you do that?

15:47.003 --> 15:48.937
I just started talking like him.

15:48.972 --> 15:50.506
I think that's all he wanted.

15:57.213 --> 15:59.815
Don't they ever get tired
of making a spectacle?

15:59.849 --> 16:02.451
Sabotaged by one of my own kids.

16:02.485 --> 16:05.621
Oh, let it go. Try to enjoy your poi.

16:05.655 --> 16:07.189
What kind of monsters are we raising?

16:07.223 --> 16:09.625
They're animals. They eat dirt.

16:09.659 --> 16:12.194
They fall off things.
They save their farts in jars.

16:12.228 --> 16:13.996
Probably put that fork in there

16:14.030 --> 16:16.999
just to see what would happen.

16:17.033 --> 16:18.467
I never said it was a fork.

16:20.870 --> 16:21.837
Sure you did.

16:21.871 --> 16:24.840
All I said was something metal.

16:24.874 --> 16:28.644
No, you said fork. I'm sure you...

16:30.413 --> 16:31.847
All right, I hated that thing.

16:31.881 --> 16:32.848
My God, it was you.

16:32.882 --> 16:34.683
Look, I told you I didn't
want it in my kitchen,

16:34.718 --> 16:37.286
which is my domain,
but you never listen!

16:37.320 --> 16:39.688
You always do things your way,
like you're Frank Sinatra.

16:39.723 --> 16:42.491
You stuck a knife in my back...
with a fork!

16:42.525 --> 16:43.529
I'm a housewife, Mike.

16:43.554 --> 16:46.295
I'm not some space woman
from "Star Trek."

16:46.329 --> 16:48.497
I want to cook normal food
my own way in my own house,

16:48.531 --> 16:50.699
except for the one night a year
when I want to eat out and go dancing

16:50.734 --> 16:52.034
because it's our anniversary!

16:52.068 --> 16:53.836
And you wanted to go to Bat Night.

16:53.870 --> 16:56.805
Wait, our... our anniversary.

16:56.840 --> 16:58.173
- Today?
- Mm.

16:58.208 --> 16:59.241
Tonight?

16:59.275 --> 17:01.977
Wh... Why didn't you tell me?

17:02.011 --> 17:03.379
I did, but you never listen.

17:03.413 --> 17:06.080
<i>It was a magnificent
coup de grace by my mother,</i>

17:06.116 --> 17:09.582
<i>particularly because
it wasn't their anniversary.</i>

17:09.607 --> 17:10.786
<i>In a tight spot, my mom was known</i>

17:10.819 --> 17:13.321
<i>to push this button
up to four times a year.</i>

17:13.356 --> 17:16.090
This was unforgivable.

17:16.126 --> 17:18.727
Peg, I...

17:18.762 --> 17:21.329
I am so sorry.

17:21.364 --> 17:23.732
Well...

17:23.767 --> 17:26.335
I'm sorry, too,

17:26.368 --> 17:29.571
for the much less bad thing that I did.

17:29.606 --> 17:32.174
I guess I wasn't listening
to you about the microwave

17:32.208 --> 17:33.575
because I was so excited thinking that

17:33.610 --> 17:34.710
I might be able to help you.

17:34.744 --> 17:37.279
Help me? With what?

17:37.313 --> 17:39.581
I see how you slave for me and the kids.

17:39.616 --> 17:42.017
Shovelling food into us all day

17:42.051 --> 17:44.186
- like it's feeding time at SeaWorld.
- Oh.

17:44.220 --> 17:45.521
I thought maybe that stupid machine

17:45.555 --> 17:47.790
could make things easier,
maybe make you happy.

17:47.824 --> 17:50.192
Oh, hon.

17:50.226 --> 17:52.887
I don't want to be happy.

17:52.912 --> 17:55.814
I like things just the way they are.

18:00.270 --> 18:03.405
I'll do a much better job
listening. I promise.

18:03.440 --> 18:05.407
I'm a big dope,
and I'd be lost without you.

18:05.442 --> 18:09.144
Okay, then.

18:09.179 --> 18:10.979
And I'll try to remember anniversaries.

18:11.014 --> 18:12.781
I guess I could write it down.

18:12.816 --> 18:16.151
Aww, don't worry. I'll remind you.

18:20.023 --> 18:22.391
Guys, wait.

18:22.425 --> 18:24.560
What if the Fotomat guy peeked
and called the authorities?

18:24.594 --> 18:26.462
Lewis is cool.
He's done jobs for me before.

18:26.496 --> 18:28.063
What if Timmy's right?

18:28.097 --> 18:30.446
Maybe just one of us should go.

18:38.174 --> 18:40.175
Good morning.

18:40.210 --> 18:42.411
The name is Jorgellington.

18:42.445 --> 18:45.080
Here you go. $11.47.

18:50.286 --> 18:52.020
Thank you!

18:57.694 --> 18:59.628
Oh, that was close.

18:59.662 --> 19:00.996
That cop might still be on my tail!

19:01.030 --> 19:02.197
You should lay low for a few days.

19:02.232 --> 19:03.765
I know a safe house in Eagle Rock.

19:03.800 --> 19:05.767
Boring stuff at Davey's place,

19:05.802 --> 19:07.169
your mom asleep on the sofa,

19:07.203 --> 19:10.439
your... mom asleep on the floor.

19:10.473 --> 19:13.642
Oh, my God. There it is.

19:13.676 --> 19:15.444
<i>The legend of Barbara Eden's
"Bob Hope Show"</i>

19:15.478 --> 19:16.945
<i>was one of those great urban myths</i>

19:16.980 --> 19:18.741
<i>which sweep across schoolyards
from time to time.</i>

19:18.766 --> 19:21.517
- Let me see it. Joey.
- <i>There was absolutely nothing to see...</i>

19:21.551 --> 19:22.595
<i>...but nearly every</i>

19:22.619 --> 19:24.152
<i>pre-pubescent boy in America</i>

19:24.153 --> 19:25.320
<i>claimed he had seen it.</i>

19:25.355 --> 19:27.523
- I've never seen anything like it.
- Me neither!

19:27.557 --> 19:28.590
I-I mean...

19:28.625 --> 19:34.029
I've seen plenty,
just not one exactly like it.

19:34.063 --> 19:36.465
You can see everything.

19:36.499 --> 19:37.866
<i>Sure, that photo was just a picture</i>

19:37.901 --> 19:39.234
<i>of Davey's brother's thumb,</i>

19:39.269 --> 19:41.236
<i>but it started me and Joey on a path</i>

19:41.271 --> 19:43.238
<i>of raunchy, wonderful boy adventures</i>

19:43.273 --> 19:44.794
<i>all through adolescence and beyond.</i>

19:44.888 --> 19:46.333
Ooh, la, la.

19:48.077 --> 19:49.504
<i>I love you, Barbara Eden.</i>

19:50.661 --> 19:53.169
<i>My dad never gave up
embracing new technology</i>

19:53.240 --> 19:55.036
<i>and trying to make things
better for my mother.</i>

19:55.099 --> 19:56.591
It's called the Strap Vac.

19:56.646 --> 19:57.613
Instead of pushing it,

19:57.647 --> 20:00.142
you carry it on your back
around the house.

20:00.197 --> 20:01.217
Less work.

20:01.251 --> 20:03.786
For who? The vacuum?

20:03.820 --> 20:05.654
<i>And he eventually repaired the microwave</i>

20:05.689 --> 20:06.956
<i>and Mom made her peace with it...</i>

20:06.990 --> 20:08.591
<i>as long as it stayed out in the garage.</i>

20:09.793 --> 20:12.428
Here you go.

20:12.462 --> 20:14.597
Mm! Toasty!

20:14.631 --> 20:16.799
You're the best cook ever, Mom!

20:19.269 --> 20:21.770
It's not even on anymore!

